    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="996" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d996">
                <head>Inhabitants of St. Maurice</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Maurice</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-12">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 12, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. President</hi>: The eminent man who fell by the
                        murderous hand of the infamous villain Booth, at the moment his soul winged
                        its flight to the celestial regions, left regrets and profound grief in our
                        hearts. The atrocious crime of which Mr. Abraham Lincoln was the victim has
                        filled us with indignation and horror.</p>
                <p>We regret the great loss to the North—the loss of a great, generous, and
                        noble-heart, who did so much for the abolition of slavery, for all his aims
                        were to do good to his fellow-man. Yet we hope that the Americans of the
                        North will finish the great work of the noble martyr, whose motto was, “<hi rend="italic">Liberty, equality and fraternity</hi>.</p>
                <p>Such is the sincere wish of the undersigned citizens of St. Maurice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>HENRY GARNY,</item>
                            <item>THOS. PRUDE,</item>
                            <item>ALBERT DEBONNAIRE,</item>
                            <item>ANTOINE DUTART,</item>
                            <item>FRANCOIS GEX,</item>
                            <item>PHILIBERT CHEVALLIER,</item>
                            <item>LOUIS SEYDOUX,</item>
                            <item>FRANCOIS BURNIER,</item>
                            <item>LOUIS SARRASIN,</item>
                            <item>F. GAY,</item>
                            <item>CHARLES VOEFFRAY,</item>
                            <item>JOSEPH DUBOULE,</item>
                            <item>JOS. MEIZOZ,</item>
                            <item>PIERRE DUFOUR,<lb/>And several others.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
